casebody.data:
IVES, Respondent, v. QUINN, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 17, 1894) Action by Grace D. Ives against Peter Quinn.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Ph. Carpenter, for appellant. Wakeman & Campbell, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for reargument denied, with $10 costs. See 28 N. Y. Supp. 267.
